      <p>
        When Canada introduced the 2021 NOC in November 2022, it replaced the old skill-level system (A, B, C, D) with <strong>Training, Education, Experience, and Responsibilities (TEER)</strong> categories numbered 0 through 5. The TEER category is encoded as the second digit of every five-digit NOC code.
      </p>

